    </omtext><omtext class="reference">
      <CMP> Clifford A. Pickover, Wonders of Numbers, Oxford University Press, pp. 116-118, 2001</CMP>
    </omtext><assertion class="example">
      <CMP> (1) 1st Collatz sequence with a(1)=1 step starts with 2=prime(1): 2-1</CMP>
    </assertion><assertion class="example">
      <CMP> (2) 1st Collatz sequence with a(3)=7 steps starts with 3=prime(2): 3-10-5-16-8-4-2-1</CMP>
    </assertion><assertion class="example">
      <CMP> (3) prime(6)=13 has Collatz sequence with 9 steps: 13-40-20-10-5-16-8-4-2-1, so has the smaller composite 12 &lt; 13: 12-6-3-10-5-16-8-4-2-1 =&gt; 9 no term of sequence</CMP>
    </assertion><assertion class="example">
